.TH "aa_simple_write_to_buffer" 9 "aa_simple_write_to_buffer" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
aa_simple_write_to_buffer \- common routine for getting policy from user
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "struct aa_loaddata *" aa_simple_write_to_buffer
.BI "(const char __user *userbuf "  ","
.BI "size_t alloc_size "  ","
.BI "size_t copy_size "  ","
.BI "loff_t *pos "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "userbuf" 12
user buffer to copy data from  (NOT NULL)
.IP "alloc_size" 12
size of user buffer (REQUIRES: \fIalloc_size\fP >= \fIcopy_size\fP)
.IP "copy_size" 12
size of data to copy from user buffer
.IP "pos" 12
position write is at in the file (NOT NULL)
.SH "RETURN"
kernel buffer containing copy of user buffer data or an
ERR_PTR on failure.
